Emmet is the plugin installed in VS code to write HTML code through it's shortcut features

Shortcuts
1. ul>li*3
<ul>
  <li></li>
  <li></li>
  <li></li>
</ul>

2. p+a+ul
<p></p>
<a href=""></a>
<ul></ul>

3. Lorem 7
Generates 7 random words 

4. class (.)  id (#)

5. p{This is a paragraph}
<p>This is a paragraph</p>

6. nav>(ul>li)*3
<nav>
    <ul>
        <li></li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
        <li></li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
        <li></li>
    </ul>
</nav>


div and span tag : Not semantic tag.
div is used to create division in webpage. Block element. It takes entire width of webpage.
span is used to take space as per content requirement. Inline element.



HTML Lists
ol  -> Ordered Lists
ul  -> Unordered Lists



HTML Tables
-> Representation of data in the form of rows and columns.

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th></th>
      <th></th>
      <th></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th></th>
      <th></th>
      <th colspan="3"></th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th rowspan="3"></th>
      <th></th>
      <th></th>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


rowspan -> That <td> data will occupy no. of rows.
colspan -> That <td> data will occupy no. of columns.

How to create a table with rowspan and colspan?
-> First arrange all data line by line using <td> and <th> using <tr>.
-> If there are lesser data in next row then also enclose all data <td> <th> using <tr>.
-> Continue till last row.
-> Now see for rowspan and colspan. and then define the property as per given in the table.

Class is similar but Id should be unique. Class is used for grouping elements.
ID is used to point to a specific style declaration in a style sheet. It is also used by JavaScript to access and manipulate the element with the specific id.

HTML Forms.
-> It is used to collect data from user and validate user's data with server.

Tags used in Forms:
1. <form></form>                              : To create HTML form for taking user input.
2. <input type="text" id="name">              : Used to take user input as text, radio buttons, checkboxes, submit button, date, number, email, password.
   <input type="radio" id="gender">           : Used to create radio button and both id's should match for single selection out of 2 else both will be selected. 
   <input type="checkbox" id="course">        : Used to create checkboxes.
   <input type="date" id="date">              : Used to take date input from user like DOB, YOP, etc.
   <input type="file" id="myFile" name="Choose File" : Used to create a file upload button

3. <label for="password">Enter Pass:</label>  : Used to create label for input. for attribute is compulsory. Input element id == label for attribute.
   <input type="text" id="password">
   
4. <input type="submit" value="Click me">     : Used to create a submit button with a label Click me on the button.
   <input type="reset" value="Reset">
5. <button>Click me</button>                  : Similar to above button

Form elements
input
label
button
placeholder : Faded text inside input box field.

select -> Drop down
option -> Drop down options
<label for="selected">Choose your dish:</label>
<select name="dishes" id="selected">
   <option value="maggi">Maggi</option>
   <option value="Kurkure">Kurkure</option>
   <option value="chips">Chips</option>
</select>
    
<textarea name="items" id="message" cols="50" rows="90"></textarea> : A plain text area to write reviews comments, compose email,etc. 

<fieldset></fieldset> : Group entire code inside a box.
<fieldset>
<legend>This is the dummy HTML Form</legend> : Used to give caption to the fieldset as heading of box.
</fieldset>

<input type="image" src="img_submit.gif" alt="Submit" width="48" height="48"> : Showing a submit button image

